execute(responseStatusCallback, jsonObject)[source]¶

This method will create a thread to execute the input command.

Parameters:

  • responseStatusCallback (func(jsonObject) ->) – A callback function has to be passed, that will send status of command execution back to the controller. This callback will be passed by the caller of execute().

  • jsonObject (dictionary) – A JSON object initially containing the command json, modified to include response information.

execute_helper(responseStatusCallback, jsonObject)[source]¶

Helper for execute().

Parameters:

  • jsonObject (dictionary) – A JSON object initially containing the command json, modified to include response information.
